{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, it also points to potential avenues for intervention.",
    "For instance, strategies that fracture the efficiency and density of these disinformation networks could be particularly impactful.",
    "As such, future research should delve into network activation and coordination mechanisms and expand to include other national and cultural contexts.",
    "Another potential intervention in these scenarios may include evidencing reasons or contexts behind specific tweets, as presented recently in Li et al. (2022), probably not to everyone in the network but depending on the characteristic of the information being sent (number of hashtags or URLs) or based on the sender/receiver.",
    "Considering our findings, recommendation systems on platforms like Twitter could be valuable targets for future intervention research."
  ]
}